    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithCompetitiveCompleteInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithCompetitiveCompleteInhibition">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#ResearchProblem"/>
        <containedIn rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#EnzymeKinetics"/>
        <specializedBy rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#InitialReactionRateOfUniUniReactionWithoutProductAndCompetitiveCompleteInhibition"/>
        <specializes rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversibleCompleteInhibition"/>
        <terms1:description xml:lang="en">uni uni reaction with inhibition</terms1:description>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Enzyme (E) and Substrate (S) form an enzyme-substrate complex (ES), which catalyzes the formation of product (P). Rates for complex formation and dissociation are k₁ and k₋₁, k₂ is the rate of the rate-determining enzymatic step of product formation. Free enzyme may bind an inhibitor (I) to form an enzyme-inhibitor complex (EI) with rates k₃ and k₋₃.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with Competitive Complete Inhibition</rdfs:label>
        <mardiID rdf:resource="https://portal.mardi4nfdi.de/wiki/Item:Q6684685"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithCompetitivePartialInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithCompetitivePartialInhibition">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#ResearchProblem"/>
        <containedIn rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#EnzymeKinetics"/>
        <specializedBy rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#InitialReactionRateOfUniUniReactionWithoutProductAndCompetitivePartialInhibition"/>
        <specializes rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversiblePartialInhibition"/>
        <terms1:description xml:lang="en">uni uni reaction with inhibition</terms1:description>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Enzyme (E) and Substrate (S) form an enzyme-substrate complex (ES), which catalyzes the formation of product (P). Rates for complex formation and dissociation are k₁ and k₋₁, k₂ is the rate of the rate-determining enzymatic step of product formation. Free enzyme and the enzyme-substrate complex may bind an inhibitor (I) to form an enzyme-inhibitor (EI) and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex (EIS) with k₃ or k₋₃ and k₄ or k₋₄ as rates of inhibitor complex formation and depletion. Enzyme-inhibitor complex and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate convert into each other with rates k₅ and k₋₅. From the enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex product is formed with rate k₂. Properly this is a mixed partial inhibition in which the inhibitor does not affect the turnover rate.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with Competitive Partial Inhibition</rdfs:label>
        <mardiID rdf:resource="https://portal.mardi4nfdi.de/wiki/Item:Q6684687"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithMixedCompleteInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithMixedCompleteInhibition">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#ResearchProblem"/>
        <containedIn rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#EnzymeKinetics"/>
        <specializedBy rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#InitialReactionRateOfUniUniReactionWithoutProductAndMixedCompleteInhibition"/>
        <specializes rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversibleCompleteInhibition"/>
        <terms1:description xml:lang="en">uni uni reaction with inhibition</terms1:description>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Enzyme (E) and Substrate (S) form an enzyme-substrate complex (ES), which catalyzes the formation of product (P). Rates for complex formation and dissociation are k₁ and k₋₁, k₂ is the rate of the rate-determining enzymatic step of product formation. Free enzyme and the enzyme-substrate complex may bind an inhibitor (I) to form an enzyme-inhibitor (EI) and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex (EIS) with k₃ or k₋₃ and k₄ or k₋₄ as rates of inhibitor complex formation and depletion. Enzyme-inhibitor complex and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate convert into each other with rates k₅ and k₋₅. From the enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex no product formation is possible, the inhibition is thus complete.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with Mixed Complete Inhibition</rdfs:label>
        <mardiID rdf:resource="https://portal.mardi4nfdi.de/wiki/Item:Q6684689"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithMixedPartialInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithMixedPartialInhibition">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#ResearchProblem"/>
        <containedIn rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#EnzymeKinetics"/>
        <specializedBy rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#InitialReactionRateOfUniUniReactionWithoutProductAndMixedPartialInhibition"/>
        <specializes rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversiblePartialInhibition"/>
        <terms1:description xml:lang="en">uni uni reaction with inhibition</terms1:description>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Enzyme (E) and Substrate (S) form an enzyme-substrate complex (ES), which catalyzes the formation of product (P). Rates for complex formation and dissociation are k₁ and k₋₁, k₂ is the rate of the rate-determining enzymatic step of product formation. Free enzyme and the enzyme-substrate complex may bind an inhibitor (I) to form an enzyme-inhibitor (EI) and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex (EIS) with k₃ or k₋₃ and  k₄ or k₋₄ as rates of inhibitor complex formation and depletion. Enzyme-inhibitor complex and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate convert into each other with rates k₅ and k₋₅. From the enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex product is formed with rate k₆.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with Mixed Partial Inhibition</rdfs:label>
        <mardiID rdf:resource="https://portal.mardi4nfdi.de/wiki/Item:Q6684690"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithNonCompetitiveCompleteInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithNonCompetitiveCompleteInhibition">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#ResearchProblem"/>
        <containedIn rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#EnzymeKinetics"/>
        <specializedBy rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#InitialReactionRateOfUniUniReactionWithoutProductAndNonCompetitiveCompleteInhibition"/>
        <specializes rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversibleCompleteInhibition"/>
        <terms1:description xml:lang="en">uni uni reaction with inhibition</terms1:description>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Enzyme (E) and Substrate (S) form an enzyme-substrate complex (ES), which catalyzes the formation of product (P). Rates for complex formation and dissociation are k₁ and k₋₁, k₂ is the rate of the rate-determining enzymatic step of product formation. Free enzyme and the enzyme-substrate complex may bind an inhibitor (I) to form an enzyme-inhibitor (EI) and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex (EIS) with k₃ or k₋₃ and k₄ or k₋₄ as rates of inhibitor complex formation and depletion. Enzyme-inhibitor complex and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate convert into each other with rates k₅ and k₋₅. In the non-competitive case: k₃ = k₄, k₋₃ = k₋₄, k₅ = k₁ and k₋₅ = k₋₁. The enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex cannot form product, the inhibition is thus complete.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with Non-Competitive Complete Inhibition</rdfs:label>
        <mardiID rdf:resource="https://portal.mardi4nfdi.de/wiki/Item:Q6684691"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithNonCompetitivePartialInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithNonCompetitivePartialInhibition">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#ResearchProblem"/>
        <containedIn rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#EnzymeKinetics"/>
        <specializedBy rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#InitialReactionRateOfUniUniReactionWithoutProductAndNonCompetitivePartialInhibition"/>
        <specializes rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversiblePartialInhibition"/>
        <terms1:description xml:lang="en">uni uni reaction with inhibition</terms1:description>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Enzyme (E) and Substrate (S) form an enzyme-substrate complex (ES), which catalyzes the formation of product (P). Rates for complex formation and dissociation are k₁ and k₋₁, k₂ is the rate of the rate-determining enzymatic step of product formation. Free enzyme and the enzyme-substrate complex may bind an inhibitor (I) to form an enzyme-inhibitor (EI) and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex (EIS) with k₋₃ and k₄ or k₋₄ as rates of inhibitor complex formation and depletion. Enzyme-inhibitor complex and enzyme-inhibitor-substrate convert into each other with rates k₅ and k₋₅. In the non-competitive case:  k₃ = k₄, k₋₃ = k₋₄, k₅ = k₁ and k₋₅ = k₋₁. The enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex can form product with rate k₆.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with Non-Competitive Partial Inhibition</rdfs:label>
        <mardiID rdf:resource="https://portal.mardi4nfdi.de/wiki/Item:Q6684692"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversibleCompleteInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversibleCompleteInhibition">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#ResearchProblem"/>
        <containedIn rdf:resource="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#EnzymeKinetics"/>
        <terms1:description xml:lang="en">uni uni reaction with inhibition</terms1:description>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with reversible inhibition. The enzyme-inhibitor-substrate complex (EIS) cannot form product, the inhibition is thus complete.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Uni Uni Reaction with Reversible Complete Inhibition</rdfs:label>
        <mardiID rdf:resource="https://portal.mardi4nfdi.de/wiki/Item:Q6684686"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversiblePartialInhibition -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://mardi4nfdi.de/mathmoddb#UniUniReactionWithReversiblePartialInhibition">
